**Abstract:**
Working notes dated October 22, 1996 titled "De Deo Fine Ultimo" with extensive quotations from Henri de Lubac on faith as movement and from Aquinas on judging by inclination versus cognition. Develops contrast between truth as correspondence in predicative statements and practical existential knowledge. Argues existential statements do not aim at intellectual assent but at practical disposition.

**AI Recommendation:** Continues 96-OCT-1 themes; develops practical knowledge epistemology. See also 96-SEP series.

